      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Could you try to manually edit the cell to give minimum gap there?\nLooking at it it should allow for enough space to shift the pin area over towards teh center of the cell.\n\nIMO this feels like blame should be not with the shapes in the cell but rather the routing choices above that choose this violation; perhaps the straps need a larger keepout than configured and it might not have been noticed earlier because it might not have hit this with other cells before.",
